6. ReRAM Graph Engine Simulation (run_reram.py)

    A Python script is provided to run NVMain for a
    ReRAM crossbar-based graph accelerator and report
    read/write latency and energy per access clearly.

    Engine model:
        - Graph engine clock         : 400 MHz (1 cycle = 2.5 ns)
        - "Number of crossbars/engine" controlled by BANKS (or XBARS alias)
        - "Crossbar dimensions"      controlled by SIZE=NxN

    Prerequisites:
        Build NVMain first (see section 2a):
        $ scons --build-type=fast

    Basic usage (uses built-in defaults):
        $ python3 run_reram.py

    Full usage:
        $ python3 run_reram.py [config] [trace] [cycles] [PARAM=value ...]

    Arguments:
        config   Path to NVMain config file
                 Default: Config/ReRAM_GraphEngine.config
        trace    Path to NVMain trace file (.nvt)
                 Default: Tests/Traces/hello_world.nvt
        cycles   Max cycles to simulate (0 = full trace)
                 Default: 0

    Special overrides (SIZE and XBARS/BANKS):
        SIZE=NxN   Set crossbar dimensions. N must be a multiple
                   of 8. Automatically sets ROWS=N, MATHeight=N,
                   COLS=N/8 and linearly scales Erd, Ewr, Eopenrd.
                   Examples: SIZE=32x32, SIZE=128x128, SIZE=256x256

        XBARS=N    Number of crossbars per engine (alias for BANKS=N).
                   Each bank models one independent NxN crossbar.
                   Examples: XBARS=1, XBARS=4, XBARS=8

    Any standard NVMain parameter can also be overridden:
        CLK=N      Engine / memory clock in MHz (e.g. CLK=800)
        BANKS=N    Same as XBARS=N

    Examples:
        # Default: 128x128 crossbar, 4 crossbars, full trace
        $ python3 run_reram.py

        # 1 crossbar, 32x32 array
        $ python3 run_reram.py Config/ReRAM_GraphEngine.config \
              Tests/Traces/hello_world.nvt 0 SIZE=32x32 XBARS=1

        # 8 crossbars, 256x256 array
        $ python3 run_reram.py Config/ReRAM_GraphEngine.config \
              Tests/Traces/hello_world.nvt 0 SIZE=256x256 XBARS=8

    Output (example, defaults):
        Read  latency  :  33.64 cycles  =   84.09 ns
        Write latency  :  42.04 cycles  =  105.10 ns
        Read  energy   :  1.7991 nJ  per access  (avg across 4 crossbars)
        Write energy   : 18.9200 nJ  per access  (avg across 4 crossbars)

    Notes on scaling:
        - Read energy scales linearly with crossbar size (bitline count),
          since wordline-driver / bitline-sense energy is per-bitline.
        - Write energy is computed per-bit (Ereset/Eset) over the fixed
          bus-transaction width and so it is intentionally size-independent
          in this model; it depends on the data bit-pattern of each write.
        - All reported latencies are in engine/memory cycles at CLK MHz.

    Device-parameter file: Config/ReRAM_GraphEngine.config


# Full size sweep, 4 crossbars per engine
`
python3 run_reram.py Config/ReRAM_GraphEngine.config Tests/Traces/hello_world.nvt 0 \
    SIZES=8x8,16x16,32x32,64x64,128x128,256x256,512x512,1024x1024 XBARS=4
`
